text: Sorry but I just see the same old tired storytelling tropes used by every single one of these movies. The only original thing about this movie is the pitch, and I'm sorry but the realistic environments with the cartoony characters looks ridiculous.   Oh no! the main character is lost/separated/taken from his single parent/family unit! He (god forbid it be a "she' for once) must travel far and wide to be reunited with his kin, aided by a quirky/non-speaking/inoffensive sidekick, and underway he will discover his true courage/power/resourcefulness/unique snowflakeness while meeting intermediate "bad guy" characters who never pose a threat because they are uncharacteristically vegetarian/caring/intellectual, and running into a bunch of cute marketable filler characters. Also, there will at some or many points be a bunch of non-verbal communication about something deeply emotional that unites all characters on a universal level, often communicated through dog-like mannerisms like small whines, puppy eyes and cuddling up against each other.  Yawn.

text: Pixar has never once failed me with any of their movies. I pretty much love every single¬†movie they ever made. And they just keep getting better! Now, they made their own¬†movie in the talking-animated-dinosaur genre, something I grew up with and loved in many classic movies! And Arlo (the main character) sincerely reminds me of Littlefoot from The Land Before Time, another movie I've loved, since my childhood! And I don't know of very many other movies that have that genre, aside from Disney's Dinosaur and the sequels to The Land Before Time. So, I'm very glad that Pixar¬†has now made their own dinosaur movie! It looks so beautiful! And I really love the¬†idea of a juvenile dinosaur bonding with a baby caveman and a family of T. rexes! It's just so cute! ^^¬†I'm 100% sure, this is gonna be very awesome in every way, being a dinosaur film and being made by Pixar!¬†I'm super hyped for this movie!

text: Frozen is trash compared to this. This is GOLD, full of talented artists work and a nice simple family friendly plot, not plagued with corny songs like Frozen. Seriously, this should be widely appreciated and marketed. The only reason frozen is popular is because of let it go and Olaf. It wasn't even a good movie. It's about someone who takes out their anger on others because of their own problems and runs away from their responsibilities. The Good Dinosaur is a good lesson that even adults should follow. No matter how tough or big you are, if you aren't scared, you aren't alive. Getting through your fears to reveal a world of adventure is WAY more fun and appealing than "let it go." And for those who complain about the cartoony and inaccurate science of the dinosaurs in this movie, look at taking fish, toys that come to life, and a society of monsters running a trans-universal career involving harvesting fear expressions from human children. This movie is one of the best out there.

text: I honestly don't get what the whole hype about this movie was. The animation is amazing but that for me was the only thing good about the movie. I gave this movie a rewatch and I still didn't enjoy it. The characters were extremely bland. The voice acting was extremely bland. The story was very boring and predictable. The message wasn't that strong. It just felt like the main character didn't need to do much but just get home. There was nothing fun about the adventure. I think this movie was not aimed at my age. But for some reason I know people my age who like this film. I wish somebody could tell me what made the film so good????? Is it because it's Pixar???? If so than that excuse is ridiculous. People need to learn that not every Pixar film is going to be a masterpiece. And I personally think this is worse than Cars 2. Cars 2 was bad but at least it wasn't boring and cliche. I personally thought this was the worst animated film of 2015. Even worse than Strange Magic, Home, Hotel Transylvania 2, and Minions. Because at least they were not boring. This is probably in my Top 20 Worst Animated Films Of All Time. All I gotta say is I can't recommend this to anyone. The movie was so overrated. People only defend it because it is Pixar. Even if the movie is good or not ( With the exception of cars 2.) All I have to say is this movie was just not meant for me. I did not enjoy it at all. Other than the animation. Look at Inside Out for an example, the animation might not be the best. But at least they put more effort in the movies plot and characters. Unlike The Good Dinosaur where they cared more about the animation than the actual movie. I give this film a 3/10. Story 3/10 Animation 10/10 Characters 3/10 "Most Overrated Movie Of 2015"
